[Adapted from the novel by Jing Mo,]

12
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:42,900
[My Lord,
Madam Doesn't Want to See You Again]

13
00:00:42,900 --> 00:00:44,780
[Episode 10]

14
00:00:50,320 --> 00:00:51,110
Ling Xiao!

15
00:00:54,600 --> 00:00:55,390
Ling Xiao!

16
00:01:06,710 --> 00:01:08,120
I knew you were keeping secrets.

17
00:01:11,480 --> 00:01:12,840
What is happening to you?

18
00:01:13,280 --> 00:01:15,000
Your body is icy cold.

19
00:01:17,950 --> 00:01:19,760
That's none of your concern.

20
00:01:19,870 --> 00:01:21,840
I can't just watch you die.

21
00:01:22,350 --> 00:01:23,710
My life is none of your concern!

22
00:01:27,560 --> 00:01:28,230
Fine.

23
00:01:29,280 --> 00:01:30,480
If you're so eager to die,

24
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:31,680
After you die,

25
00:01:31,680 --> 00:01:33,040
I'll make Niyue's life miserable.

26
00:01:33,400 --> 00:01:34,920
And our marriage will be invalid.

27
00:01:37,560 --> 00:01:38,920
Not on my watch.

28
00:01:41,150 --> 00:01:42,590
You still care about Niyue.

29
00:01:44,350 --> 00:01:44,950
Let's go.

30
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:27,840
How do you feel?

31
00:02:31,910 --> 00:02:32,800
Lie down and rest.

32
00:02:33,470 --> 00:02:33,910
Come on.

33
00:03:07,630 --> 00:03:09,520
Is this another relapse
from the poisoning?

34
00:03:13,960 --> 00:03:14,710
Ling Xiao?

35
00:03:19,780 --> 00:03:25,420
♪The weathered years,
the yellow old marks♪

36
00:03:25,500 --> 00:03:31,540
♪Memories of a lifetime
in the past dreams♪

37
00:03:31,700 --> 00:03:37,340
♪The residual snow, the shining stars,
the hazy midnight moon♪

38
00:03:37,620 --> 00:03:42,820
♪Strong liquor cannot dispel
the melancholy of love♪

39
00:03:43,460 --> 00:03:48,980
♪The green mountains form a line
and the river reflects the moon♪

40
00:03:49,630 --> 00:03:50,750
Why is your body still cold?

41
00:03:55,020 --> 00:04:01,060
♪Spring returns with warmth again,
and birds are everywhere♪

42
00:04:01,340 --> 00:04:06,140
♪This love only awaits
your reciprocation♪

43
00:04:06,460 --> 00:04:12,220
♪Who will hold my hand now?
Your beautiful smile can make me drunk♪

44
00:04:17,630 --> 00:04:18,750
I've tried everything.

45
00:04:19,430 --> 00:04:20,920
Not only is his body not warming up,

46
00:04:21,600 --> 00:04:22,950
but it's getting even colder.

47
00:04:25,720 --> 00:04:26,480
It seems

48
00:04:27,870 --> 00:04:29,070
there's no other way.

49
00:04:47,780 --> 00:04:53,380
♪The lone snowy peak is unable
to reach the moon♪

50
00:04:53,460 --> 00:04:59,980
♪Gatherings and partings are fated,
love also has its sorrow or joy♪

51
00:05:00,460 --> 00:05:04,500
♪My concern
sinks into the long night♪

52
00:05:04,580 --> 00:05:08,500
♪May I be bold to ask what love means?♪

53
00:05:08,580 --> 00:05:14,340
♪In the flickering candlelight,
I dream of a glimpse of her♪

54
00:05:14,780 --> 00:05:18,140
♪In my dreams,
the past remains unchanged♪

55
00:05:18,260 --> 00:05:21,620
♪In my lifetime, sorrows
and joys become a book♪

56
00:05:21,820 --> 00:05:28,020
♪I write the rest of my life
with one stroke♪

57
00:05:28,860 --> 00:05:32,220
♪The morning is full of joy♪

58
00:05:32,380 --> 00:05:36,180
♪The evening is full of melancholy♪

59
00:05:36,340 --> 00:05:42,500
♪Miss you a lifetime
with love engraved in my bones♪

60
00:05:43,100 --> 00:05:46,540
♪One smile to outshine the world♪

61
00:05:46,620 --> 00:05:50,100
♪One glimpse to connect the hearts♪

62
00:05:50,220 --> 00:05:57,100
♪One hug to witness the end of destiny,
but how can we part?♪

63
00:05:57,220 --> 00:06:00,700
♪One glance to see the familiar scenery♪

64
00:06:00,780 --> 00:06:04,460
♪One thought
to relive the beginning of us♪

65
00:06:04,780 --> 00:06:10,700
♪May we meet again
after countless cycles♪

66
00:06:50,160 --> 00:06:50,830
You're awake.

67
00:06:51,800 --> 00:06:52,600
Are you all right now?

68
00:07:28,160 --> 00:07:28,950
So...

69
00:07:29,360 --> 00:07:31,430
I did it out of honor.

70
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:32,630
I know.

71
00:07:33,720 --> 00:07:35,000
No personal feelings.

72
00:07:35,750 --> 00:07:36,600
I'm glad you know.

73
00:07:38,430 --> 00:07:39,560
Figure out how to go back.

74
00:07:47,920 --> 00:07:48,830
I am awake,

75
00:07:49,360 --> 00:07:50,360
but I'm not healed.

76
00:07:53,510 --> 00:07:54,750
You haven't recovered?

77
00:07:55,560 --> 00:07:56,560
What happened to you?

78
00:07:59,000 --> 00:08:00,680
A cold syndrome
from when I trained as a child.

79
00:08:01,630 --> 00:08:03,160
I get a relapse every full moon.

80
00:08:05,270 --> 00:08:06,240
It can't be healed so easily.

81
00:08:07,600 --> 00:08:10,160
You're suffering from
the side effects of the secret art.

82
00:08:10,950 --> 00:08:11,830
Is it worth it?

83
00:08:13,160 --> 00:08:14,390
Every goal

84
00:08:15,190 --> 00:08:16,160
comes with a price.

85
00:08:18,240 --> 00:08:20,040
Achieve the goal by any means necessary.

86
00:08:20,750 --> 00:08:21,680
It's who you are.

87
00:08:23,510 --> 00:08:24,800
You are just as stubborn yourself.

88
00:08:25,720 --> 00:08:26,720
You never turn back

89
00:08:27,480 --> 00:08:28,600
despite all the obstacles.

90
00:08:29,680 --> 00:08:30,630
When you put it that way,

91
00:08:31,430 --> 00:08:33,390
we have a lot in common.

92
00:08:54,080 --> 00:08:55,670
Had we met
under different circumstances,

93
00:08:57,240 --> 00:08:58,550
it could've changed everything.

94
00:09:00,510 --> 00:09:01,000
We might

95
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:03,030
become friends.

96
00:09:04,910 --> 00:09:06,960
I'm not the best person
you want as a friend.

97
00:09:07,750 --> 00:09:08,870
What would you be, then?

98
00:09:11,960 --> 00:09:12,790
I'd say

99
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:15,270
let bygones be bygones.

100
00:09:16,080 --> 00:09:16,720
Look forward

101
00:09:17,150 --> 00:09:18,080
to the future.

102
00:09:20,510 --> 00:09:22,440
The future is full of uncertainties.

103
00:09:23,510 --> 00:09:24,720
It's far from our reach.

104
00:09:25,240 --> 00:09:26,320
How do we look forward to it?

105
00:09:27,840 --> 00:09:29,200
Perhaps it's best to go with the flow.

106
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:31,670
Does that mean

107
00:09:32,360 --> 00:09:33,840
you've never thought about your future?

108
00:09:34,840 --> 00:09:35,670
I have.

109
00:09:37,840 --> 00:09:40,600
I met a young man once.

110
00:09:41,750 --> 00:09:43,270
I will never forget that memory.

111
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:46,270
There were moments

112
00:09:47,080 --> 00:09:49,360
when I wanted to brew tea, make wine,

113
00:09:49,870 --> 00:09:50,910
play the Guqin, wield the sword,

114
00:09:52,030 --> 00:09:53,510
and admire the flowers
together with him.

115
00:09:54,030 --> 00:09:54,840
It seems

116
00:09:54,840 --> 00:09:56,150
you already have someone in mind.

117
00:09:57,440 --> 00:09:59,080
But that was ages ago.

118
00:10:00,030 --> 00:10:01,150
I've moved on

119
00:10:01,150 --> 00:10:02,630
from having unrealistic dreams.

120
00:10:02,790 --> 00:10:03,360
Yes.

121
00:10:03,960 --> 00:10:05,000
There's no need to dream

122
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:06,150
when he's next to you.

123
00:10:07,440 --> 00:10:08,720
He's not around.

124
00:10:10,120 --> 00:10:10,840
Besides,

125
00:10:12,030 --> 00:10:14,240
you have Niyue with you.

126
00:10:15,150 --> 00:10:15,630
Niyue...

127
00:10:17,120 --> 00:10:18,360
Niyue is special.

128
00:10:22,550 --> 00:10:23,240
When I was young,

129
00:10:24,720 --> 00:10:25,790
I was at the most helpless

130
00:10:25,790 --> 00:10:27,120
and perilous time of my life.

131
00:10:27,480 --> 00:10:28,790
She came into my life.

132
00:10:30,200 --> 00:10:32,320
She was the one firefly
in that darkness.

133
00:10:34,270 --> 00:10:36,080
Now I know why you always defend her.

134
00:10:37,670 --> 00:10:39,200
I will give you the justice you deserve.

135
00:10:40,750 --> 00:10:41,750
You want to take responsibility

136
00:10:42,150 --> 00:10:43,150
for her mistake?

137
00:10:44,630 --> 00:10:45,200
You know.

138
00:10:45,750 --> 00:10:46,910
I'm not talking about that.

139
00:10:48,030 --> 00:10:49,270
How can I know if you don't say it?

140
00:10:49,510 --> 00:10:50,360
Will you answer

141
00:10:51,480 --> 00:10:52,750
if I tell you?

142
00:10:56,380 --> 00:11:00,140
♪The mountains and rivers
I've seen are painted on the fan♪

143
